      {
         "text": "### This is mine… Are you sure?\n\nRelying solely on what is written in texts can be problematic, as they may employ literary devices (<htcite0>) that are not understood by everyone. Faced with this scenario, we need evidence that allows us to confirm ideas. Fossils are an example of such evidence.\n\n#### What is our origin?\n\nWhen discussing our origin, it is not uncommon to see people thinking only of our own species, often due to a lack of knowledge about the true age of the planet or how species emerge.\n\nThanks to advances in knowledge, we now know that, although we are the only living species of the genus *Homo*, other species emerged before us, and their origin was precisely the African continent (<htcite1>). Among the species highlighted in this text is *Homo rudolfensis*, which lived between <htdate0> and <htdate1>, whose skull is shown in *Figure 2*:",
         "source": [
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "0c59c0de-f385-4bf2-8190-166d53e158b5",
               "text": "Portuese, Ludovico & Pallavidini, Marta",
               "page": "",
               "date_time": {
