      {
         "text": "#### *Homo* in Zimbabwe\n\nThe earliest evidence of the arrival of species carrying technology consists of worked stone fragments, developed using a technique known as the Levallois core (**Figure 4**). However, it is not possible to say with certainty that they were produced by humans like us (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).",
         "source": [
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "27f40b72-c752-48bc-8fd5-e846e9d62c34",
               "text": "Brantingham, P. J., & Kuhn, S. L.",
               "page": "pp. 747 - 748",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "2001",
                  "month": "",
                  "day": ""
               }
            },
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "0c717575-d51a-464d-9be6-8ecfda771376",
               "text": "History Tracers Team",
               "page": "The Great Zimbabwe",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "2025",
                  "month": "",
                  "day": ""
               }
            }
         ],
         "date_time": null,
         "isTable": false,
         "imgdesc": "",
         "format": "markdown",
         "PostMention": ""
      },
      {
         "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><img src=\"images/Louvre/0000166561_OG.JPG\" id=\"imgLVR\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgLVR', '0%')\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 4</b>: Levallois Core. © Musée du Louvre/ Département des Antiquités égyptiennes (<htcite0>).</p>",
         "source": [
            {
               "type": 0,
               "uuid": "1c47caa3-225d-406b-83a8-a53306bea630",
               "text": "Musée du Louvre",
               "page": "",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
