            }
         ],
         "date_time": null,
         "isTable": false,
         "imgdesc": "",
         "format": "html",
         "PostMention": " "
      },
      {
         "text": "Thus, we need more solid evidence to confirm the presence of *Homo sapiens* in this location.\n\n#### Bantu People\n\nCurrently, most inhabitants of Zimbabwe speak the Shona language, which belongs to the Bantu group (<htcite0>).\n\nThe Bantu people originated in a region where Cameroon is located today, with archaeological evidence indicating settlement from at least <htdate0> (<htcite1>; <htcite2>; <htcite3>).\n\nThe arrival of Bantu peoples in the Zimbabwe region dates to between <htdate1> and <htdate2> (<htcite4>), and when they arrived, other human groups were already living there.\n\n#### General Analysis\n\nIn this introduction to the Mutapa State, we have already learned the following information obtained from evidence (fossils are evidence that some living being was present in a location) on the African continent:\n- The genus *Homo*, which encompasses different species, including our own, has been in Africa for millions of years (<htcite5>);\n- The presence of *Homo* species in southern Africa also dates back thousands of years (<htcite6>);\n- Bantu-speaking peoples, such as Shona speakers, have been in the region for thousands of years (<htcite7>).\n\nDespite all this evidence, in <htdate3>, in Europe—thousands of kilometers away—it was established that not only Africa but the world would belong to peoples who had never lived in those places for long periods. This occurred through a document known as the Treaty of Tordesillas (<htcite8>), leading us to the following reflection:",
         "source": [
